Shares of the following companies may
have  unusual  moves in  Canadian trading .  Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc.  (POT CT): Options traders
are boosting wagers that BHP Billiton Ltd. and potential rivals
will bid higher than the $40 billion already offered by the
world’s biggest mining company for Potash.  Research In Motion Ltd.  (RIM CT): The maker of the
BlackBerry smartphone was given a new “hold” rating at ISI
Group Inc. The price estimate is $60.  To contact the reporter on this story:
